main event: A radar observation detected a UFO in Long Beach, California on July 14, 1956.
interesting points: The object was slightly larger than a B-29 aircraft and remained stationary on radar for 45 days before disappearing., The sighting lasted 30 minutes., The radar observation concluded it was not an aircraft, airborne radar, or astronomical., The officer suggested it might be a known planet object mentioned in other cases., The document originated from Project Blue Book, an official USAF program to investigate UFOs.
witness description: The observation was made under clear and calm conditions during exceptional visibility.
